'''拉丁音乐'''（{{lang-en|Latin Music}}，[[葡萄牙语|葡萄牙语]]与[[西班牙语|西班牙语]]：música latina）是[[音乐产业|音乐产业]]中的一种流派，笼统地表示源自西班牙语及葡萄牙语地区（即[[伊比利亚美洲|伊比利亚美洲]]和[[伊比利亚半岛|伊比利亚半岛]]）的音乐，也表示用这两种语言演唱的音乐。<ref name="morales">{{cite book |last1=Morales |first1=Ed |title=The Latin beat: The Rhythms and Roots of Latin music From Bossa Nova to Salsa and Beyond |date=2003 |publisher=[[Da_Capo_Press|Da Capo Press]] |location=Cambridge, MA |isbn=978-0-306-81018-3 |page=xiii |edition=1. Da Capo Press |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Lpv25quOSnwC&lpg=PR13 |accessdate=2015-09-10 |quote=Including Spain, there are twenty-two predominately Spanish-speaking countries, and there are many more styles of Latin music. |archive-date=2017-02-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207215524/https://books.google.com/books?id=Lpv25quOSnwC&lpg=PR13 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="stavans">{{cite book |last1=Stavans |first1=llan |authorlink=Ilan Stavans |title=Latin music: musicians, genres, and themes |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qE-LBAAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PR18#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=2014 |publisher=[[ABC-CLIO|ABC-CLIO]] |location=Santa Barbara, California: |isbn=978-0-313-34396-4 |page=xviii, 838 |accessdate=2014-10-30 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001413/https://books.google.com/books?id=qE-LBAAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PR18#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="vivalatino">{{cite journal |last1=Lawrence |first1=Larry |last2=Wright |first2=Tom |title=¡Viva Latino! |journal=[[Billboard_(magazine)|Billboard]] |date=1985-01-26 |volume=97 |issue=4 |pages=53, 62 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7CQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PT109#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2015-04-09 |issn=0006-2510 |archive-date=2016-05-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160519042109/https://books.google.com/books?id=7CQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PT109#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="rosaldo">{{cite book |last1=Flores |first1=Juan |last2=Rosaldo |first2=Renato |title=A Companion to Latina/o Studies. |date=2007 |publisher=Blackwell Pub. |location=Oxford |isbn=978-0-470-65826-0 |page=50 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i3a1qVqHoJAC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA50#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2015-09-10 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001422/https://books.google.com/books?id=i3a1qVqHoJAC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA50#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Llewellyn |first1=Howell |title=ShowMarket to Focus on Development of Latin Music |journal=Billboard |date=1995-11-25 |volume=107 |issue=47 |page=72 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pw0EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA72#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2015-07-30 |issn=0006-2510 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001427/https://books.google.com/books?id=Pw0EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA72#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Arenas |first1=Fernando |title=Lusophone Africa: Beyond Independence |date=2011 |publisher=University of Minnesota Press |location=Minneapolis |isbn=978-0-8166-6983-7 |page=220 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eThbx7A_mEEC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA220#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2015-09-10 |archive-date=2020-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806034344/https://books.google.com/books?id=eThbx7A_mEEC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA220#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Stavans |first1=Ilan |last2=Augenbraum |first2=Harold |title=Encyclopedia Latina : history, culture, and society in the United States |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopedialati02stav |date=2005 |publisher=Grolier Academic Reference |location=Danbury, Conn. |isbn=978-0-7172-5818-5 |page=[https://archive.org/details/encyclopedialati02stav/page/201 201] |quote=The term Latin music identifies a wide range of genres and styles generated in Latin America and the Iberian Peninsula}}</ref>

== 术语和分类 ==
黛博拉·帕齊尼·埃爾南德斯（{{lang-es|Deborah Pacini Hernández}}）指出，由于20世纪50年代居住在[[纽约|纽约]]的拉丁裔移民主要是[[波多黎各|波多黎各]]人和[[古巴|古巴]]人后裔，而当时的纽约在音乐界占有主导地位，所以“拉丁音乐”被刻板地定义为源自原[[西属西印度群岛|西属西印度群岛]]地区的音乐。她还观察到，甚至20世纪60年代流行的[[巴萨诺瓦|巴萨诺瓦]]、以及受[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]音乐影响的{{link-en|赫伯· 阿尔珀特|Herb Alpert}}，都没有改变这种刻板印象。<ref name="rosaldo"/>后来，音乐产业才将所有用[[西班牙语|西班牙语]]和[[葡萄牙语|葡萄牙语]]演唱的音乐称之为拉丁音乐，包括西班牙和葡萄牙的音乐。<ref name="rosaldo"/> 

在纽约拉美裔的抗议活动后，{{link-en|美国国家录音艺术与科学学会|The Recording Academy}}（NARAS）于1975年为[[格莱美奖|格莱美奖]]新增了一项名为{{link-en|格莱美最佳拉丁乐录制|Grammy Award for Best Latin Recording|最佳拉丁乐录制}}的奖项。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Gebesmair |first1=Andreas |title=Global Repertoires : Popular Music Within and Beyond the Transnational Music Industry. |date=2001 |publisher=Taylor and Francis |isbn=9781138275201 |page=63 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aS8rDwAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PA63#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2019-07-17 |archive-date=2020-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200906153433/https://books.google.com/books?id=aS8rDwAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PA63#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>对此，恩里克·费尔南德斯（{{lang-es|Enrique Fernandez}}）在[[公告牌_(杂志)|公告牌杂志]]上写道，拉丁音乐只拥有一个奖项，意味着所有的拉丁音乐流派都要在一起竞争，即使它们彼此差异巨大。他还指出，这一荣誉在大多数时候都颁给了{{link-en|热带音乐|Tropical Music}}的表演者。八年后，该组织新增了三个拉丁音乐奖项：{{link-en|格莱美最佳拉丁流行专辑|Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album|最佳拉丁流行专辑}}、{{link-en|格莱美最佳墨西哥/墨西哥-美国专辑|Grammy Award for Best Mexican/Mexican-American Album|最佳墨西哥/墨西哥-美国专辑}}、{{link-en|格莱美最佳热带拉丁专辑|Grammy Award for Best Tropical Latin Album|最佳热带拉丁专辑}}。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Fernandez |first1=Enrique |title=NARAS Takes A Welcome Step |journal=Billboard |date=1983-06-18 |page=73 |issn=0006-2510}}</ref>拉丁流行是一种笼统的说法，可以表示任何用西班牙语演唱的[[流行歌曲|流行歌曲]]；而墨西哥/墨西哥-美国音乐（也叫{{link-en|墨西哥地区音乐|Regional Mexican}}）是源自墨西哥、或者受墨西哥裔美国人影响的音乐风格，包括{{link-en|特哈诺音乐|Tejano music}}；热带音乐则专指源于原西属西印度群岛地区的音乐。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Fernandez|first1=Enrique|title=Latin Notas|journal=[[Billboard_(magazine)|Billboard]]|date=1986-11-01|volume=98|issue=44|page=40A|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9CMEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=RA1-PA40&dq=%22latin%20pop%22%20latin%20music&pg=RA1-PA40#v=onepage&q&f=false|accessdate=2015-03-22|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205001446/https://books.google.com/books?id=9CMEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=RA1-PA40&dq=%22latin%20pop%22%20latin%20music&pg=RA1-PA40#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>

1997年，NARAS建立了{{link-en|拉丁录音学院|Latin Recording Academy}}（LARAS），以扩大其在拉丁美洲和西班牙的事务。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Lannert|first1=John|title=LARAS Formed To Expand Latin Work of NARAS|journal=Billboard|date=1997-06-21|volume=109|issue=25|pages=6, 92|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KBAEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA6#v=onepage&q&f=false|accessdate=2016-08-01|archive-date=2020-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001517/https://books.google.com/books?id=KBAEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA6#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>2000年9月，LARAS推出[[拉丁格莱美|拉丁格莱美]]作为一项独立于格莱美的颁奖礼。格莱美的组织者表示，拉丁音乐的领域太过庞大，不适合附属于格莱美。NARAS的前负责人{{link-en|迈克尔·格林|Michael Greene}}（{{lang-en|Michael Greene}}）称，拉丁格莱美奖的创建过程是很复杂的，因为拉丁音乐风格多样，它们唯一的共同点只是语言。因此，拉丁格莱美颁给用[[西班牙语|西班牙语]]或[[葡萄牙语|葡萄牙语]]演唱的歌曲<ref name="oneword">{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2000/sep/12/news/ss-19479|title=One Little Word, Yet It Means So Much|last=Valdes-Rodriguez|first=Alisa|work=Los Angeles Times|publisher=Tribune Company|date=2000-09-12|accessdate=2013-12-25|archive-date=2013-12-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131229065435/http://articles.latimes.com/2000/sep/12/news/ss-19479|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而该组织专注于来自拉丁美洲、西班牙和葡萄牙的音乐。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fernandez|first1=Enrique|title=After Birthing Pains, Latin Grammys Should Grow Strong|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2000-03-05/entertainment/0003031244_1_latin-music-latin-academy-latin-grammy-show|accessdate=2017-03-09|work=[[Sun-Sentinel|Sun-Sentinel]]|date=2000-03-05|archive-date=2017-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810012829/http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2000-03-05/entertainment/0003031244_1_latin-music-latin-academy-latin-grammy-show|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

20世纪90年代末以来，[[拉丁裔美国人|拉丁裔美国人]]的人口大幅增加<ref>{{cite book |last1=Suárez-Orozco |first1=Marcelo |title=Latinos: Remaking America |url=https://archive.org/details/latinosremakinga0000unse |date=2008 |publisher=University of California Press |isbn=978-0-520-25827-3}}</ref>，美国音乐产业开始把任何主要用西班牙语演唱的音乐称为“拉丁音乐”。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Avant-Mier |first1=Roberto |title=Rock the Nation: Latin/o Identities and the Latin Rock Diaspora |date=2010 |publisher=Continuum Publishing Corporation}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Edwards |first1=Bob |title=Profile: Latin Grammys at the Staples Center in Los Angeles |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-31750825.html |website=[[NPR|NPR]] |accessdate=2015-08-07 |date=2000-09-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160225024337/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-31750825.html |archivedate=2016-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Barkley |first1=Elizabeth F. |title=Crossroads: the Multicultural Roots of America's Popular Music |date=2007 |publisher=Pearson Prentice Hall |location=Upper Saddle River, NJ |isbn=978-0-13-193073-5 |page=232 |edition=2nd |quote=The U.S. record industry defines Latin music as simply any release with lyrics that are mostly in Spanish.}}</ref>根据这个定义，任何类型的西班牙语歌曲都被归类为拉丁音乐。<ref>{{cite news |last1=Valdes-Rodriguez |first1=Alisa |title=The Loud and Quiet Explosions |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1999/dec/26/entertainment/ca-47489 |accessdate=2015-10-28 |work=Los Angeles Times |publisher=Tribune Company |date=1999-12-26 |archive-date=2015-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123002759/http://articles.latimes.com/1999/dec/26/entertainment/ca-47489 |dead-url=no }}</ref>同时，这也让用西班牙语演唱的西班牙艺术家被贴上“拉丁歌手”的标签。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cobo |first1=Leila |title=What 'Latin' Means Now, In Music and Beyond |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8507562/latin-meaning-today-music-analysis |website=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |accessdate=2019-07-17 |date=2019-04-18 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308195756/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8507562/latin-meaning-today-music-analysis |dead-url=no }}</ref> 

[[美国唱片工业协会|美国唱片工业协会]]（{{lang-en|Recording Industry Association of America}}，RIAA）和公告牌杂志采用拉丁音乐的这一定义来追踪西班牙语唱片在美国的销售情况<ref>{{cite web |title=RIAA 2015 Year-End Latin Sales & Shipments Data Report |url=https://www.riaa.com/reports/riaa-2015-year-end-latin-sales-shipments-data-report-riaa/ |website=RIAA |accessdate=2019-07-20 |date=2015 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308144921/https://www.riaa.com/reports/riaa-2015-year-end-latin-sales-shipments-data-report-riaa/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1099596/latin-sales-down-slightly-in-2011-digital-latin-sales-up |title=Latin Sales Down Slightly In 2011, Digital Latin Sales Up |last=Cobo |first=Leila |authorlink=Leila Cobo |journal=Billboard |date=2012-01-05 |accessdate=2015-09-30 |archive-date=2018-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613185635/https://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1099596/latin-sales-down-slightly-in-2011-digital-latin-sales-up |dead-url=no }}</ref>2000年，RIAA为拉丁音乐专辑和单曲开设了与其标准认证门槛不同的黄金与白金奖。<ref>{{cite web |title=RIAA Updates Latin Gold & Platinum Program |url=https://www.riaa.com/riaa-updates-latin-gold-platinum-program/ |website=RIAA |accessdate=2019-07-20 |date=2013-12-20 |archive-date=2018-06-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180624173010/https://www.riaa.com/riaa-updates-latin-gold-platinum-program/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>公告牌将其拉丁音乐榜单分为三个子类别：拉丁流行、墨西哥地区音乐以及热带音乐。<ref name=Nielsen>{{cite journal|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=CxAEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA4&dq=intitle:billboard+%22latin+albums%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=90L6UNLsMYuY9QS-qoHIDg&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Billboard's Latin Charts Switch To SoundScan|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|pages=4, 71|date=1993-07-10|accessdate=2013-01-19|journal=|archive-date=2017-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525083953/https://books.google.com/books?id=CxAEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA4&dq=intitle:billboard+%22latin+albums%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=90L6UNLsMYuY9QS-qoHIDg&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>21世纪00年代中期，随着拉丁城市音乐流派（如{{link-en|拉丁嘻哈|Latin Hiphop}}、{{link-en|雷鬼凍|Reggaeton}}）的兴起，又新增了第四个子类别。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Cobo |first1=Leila |title=New Latin Charts Bow |journal=Billboard |date=2005-05-21 |volume=117 |issue=21 |page=10 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kRQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA10#v=onepage&q&f=false |publisher=Nielsen Business Media |issn=0006-2510 |access-date=2019-08-14 |archive-date=2021-02-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226143302/https://books.google.com/books?id=kRQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&pg=PA10#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 历史 ==
=== 20世纪40-50年代 ===
由于[[拉丁裔美国人|拉丁裔美国人]]对美国音乐市场的影响越来越大，“拉丁音乐”一词在美国诞生，著名的先驱包括{{link-en|沙維爾·庫加|Xavier Cugat}}（40年代）和{{link-en|提托‧普安提|Tito Puente}}（50年代）等。<ref name="stavans" /><ref name="vivalatino" />正如一位作家对40年代这股热潮的解释那样，“以未被卷入[[第二次世界大战|第二次世界大战]]的[[拉丁美洲|拉丁美洲]]为主题的音乐和电影，是最受那些想暂时忘却灾难的美国人喜爱的。”<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_Ynt6yc5nGQC&pg=PT263 |title=Skylark: The Life and Times of Johnny Mercer |first=Philip |last=Furia |publisher=Macmillan |year=2004 |isbn=978-1-4668-1923-8 |page=263 |access-date=2019-08-14 |archive-date=2017-02-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214224413/https://books.google.com/books?id=_Ynt6yc5nGQC&pg=PT263 |dead-url=no }}</ref>战时“[[睦邻政策|睦邻政策]]”的[[政治宣传|政治宣传]]，更加强了这种文化影响。<ref>{{cite book |first=Brian |last=O'Neil |chapter=Carmen Miranda: The High Price of Fame and Bananas |title=Latina Legacies |url=https://archive.org/details/latinalegaciesid00ruiz |editor1-first=Vicki L. |editor1-last=Ruiz |editor2-first=Virginia |editor2-last=Sánchez Korrol |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2005 |page=[https://archive.org/details/latinalegaciesid00ruiz/page/195 195] |isbn=978-0-19-515398-9 |quote=the power that Hollywood films could exert in the two-pronged campaign to win the hearts and minds of Latin Americans and to convince Americans of the benefits of Pan-American friendship}}</ref>作为一名作曲家，{{link-en|培瑞兹·普拉多|Pérez Prado}}有{{link-en|Mambo No. 5|Mambo No. 5}}和Mambo No. 8等代表作。在1955年曼波运动的高峰，他以“樱桃粉与苹果花白”（{{lang-en|Cherry Pink and Apple Blossom White}}）一曲的{{link-en|恰恰恰 (音乐)|cha-cha-chá|恰恰恰}}版本登上了美国榜单的第一名。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/p%C3%A9rez-prado-mn0000310383 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-10-11 |archive-date=2019-10-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191023202303/https://www.allmusic.com/artist/p%C3%A9rez-prado-mn0000310383 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 20世纪60年代 ===
巴西人的[[巴萨诺瓦|巴萨诺瓦]]开始在拉丁美洲广泛传播，之后尤其在[[安东尼奥·卡洛斯·裘宾|安东尼奥·卡洛斯·裘宾]]的领导下，它开始成为国际潮流。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Taffet |first1=Jeffrey |last2=Watcher |first2=Dustin |title=Latin America and the United States: A Documentary History |date=2011 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=New York |isbn=978-0-19-538568-7 |edition=2nd |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OhC9DgAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PT419#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2017-06-07 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001602/https://books.google.com/books?id=OhC9DgAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PT419#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{link-en|Rock en español|Rock en español}}（意为“用西班牙语摇滚”）开始在拉丁美洲的年轻一代中流行，<ref>{{cite book |authorlink1=Cordelia Candelaria |last1=Candelari |first1=Cordelia |editor1-last=Candelaria |editor1-first=Cordelia |editor2-last=García |editor2-first=Peter J. |editor3-last=Aldama |editor3-first=Arturo J. |title=Encyclopedia of Latino Popular Culture in the United States |volume=2 |date=2004 |publisher=Greenwood Press |location=Westport, CT |isbn=978-0-313-32215-0 |page=690 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3uD6PKXl3q4C&lpg=PP1&pg=PA690#v=onepage&q&f=false |access-date=2019-08-14 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001607/https://books.google.com/books?id=3uD6PKXl3q4C&lpg=PP1&pg=PA690#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>这也包括{{link-en|Almendra (乐队)|Almendra (band)|Almendra}}等阿根廷乐队。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Olsen |first1=Dale |last2=Sheehy |first2=Daniel E. |title=The Garland handbook of Latin American music |date=2008 |publisher=Routledge |location=New York |isbn=978-0-415-96101-1 |page=458 |edition=2nd |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RK6TAgAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PA458#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2017-06-07 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001611/https://books.google.com/books?id=RK6TAgAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PA458#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>墨西哥裔美国{{link-en|拉丁摇滚|Latin rock}}小提琴手[[卡洛斯·山塔那|卡洛斯·山塔那]]也开始他长达数十年的流行生涯。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/carlos-santana-mn0000175196/biography |title=Carlos Santana: Biography |last=Ruhlmann |first=William |year=2003 |publisher=AllMusic |accessdate=2017-06-07 |archive-date=2021-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227073818/https://www.allmusic.com/artist/carlos-santana-mn0000175196/biography |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 20世纪70年代 ===
[[File:Julio_Iglesias_(Spanje),_Bestanddeelnr_923-3697.jpg|thumb]]在2013年被[[吉尼斯世界纪录|吉尼斯世界纪录]]认证为史上最畅销的男性拉丁艺术家。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2013/4/julio-iglesias-receives-world-record-certificate-in-beijing-47865/ |title=Julio Iglesias receives world record certificate in Beijing |publisher=Guinness World Record |date=2013-04-02 |accessdate=2013-12-24 |archive-date=2013-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226060633/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2013/4/julio-iglesias-receives-world-record-certificate-in-beijing-47865/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>]]
[[骚沙音乐|骚沙音乐]]成为70年代热带音乐的主导流派。{{link-en|Fania Records|Fania Records}}在推广骚沙音乐方面广受认可，其旗下{{link-en|魯賓・布雷|Rubén Blades}}、{{link-en|赫克托·拉维|Héctor Lavoe}}、{{link-en|希莉亚·库兹|Celia Cruz}}等艺人扩大了骚沙音乐的听众。
<ref>{{cite book |last1=Bernstein |first1=Arthur |last2=Sekine |first2=Naoki |last3=Weismann |first3=Dick |title=The Global Music Industry Three Perspectives. |date=2013 |publisher=Taylor and Francis |location=Hoboken |isbn=978-1-135-92248-1 |page=78 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oTnaAAAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PA78#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2017-06-06 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001627/https://books.google.com/books?id=oTnaAAAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PA78#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>70年代末，[[胡利奥·伊格莱西亚斯|胡利奥·伊格莱西亚斯]]、[[卡米洛·塞斯托|卡米洛·塞斯托]]、{{link-en|拉斐尔 (歌手)|Raphael (singer)|拉斐尔}}等一批{{link-en|拉丁民谣|Latin Ballad}}歌手涌入拉丁美洲的音乐榜单和美国的拉丁市场。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Salaverri |first1=Fernando |title=Spain Establishing the Latin European Link |journal=Billboard |date=1979-11-03 |volume=91 |issue=44 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zCQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PT115#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2017-03-24 |issn=0006-2510 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001633/https://books.google.com/books?id=zCQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PT115#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>1972年，{{link-en|Organización de Telecomunicaciones de Iberoamérica|伊比利亚-美洲电信组织}}（{{lang-es|Organización de Telecomunicaciones de Iberoamérica}}，OTI）创建了{{link-en|OTI音乐节|OTI Festival}}，作为歌曲创作比赛将伊比利亚-美洲国家（包括拉丁美洲，西班牙和葡萄牙）联系在一起。公告牌的拉米罗·伯尔（{{lang-en|Ramiro Burr}}）指出，这一比赛被认为是“拉丁音乐界最大、最负盛名的歌曲创作节”。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Burr |first1=Ramiro |title=Mexican Quartet Captures Top OTI Prize |journal=Billboard |date=1991-01-05 |page=61 }}</ref>

=== 20世纪80年代 ===
80年代，拉丁民谣仍然是拉丁流行音乐的主要形式，{{link-en|胡安·加布里埃尔|Juan Gabriel}}、{{link-en|José José|José José}}、胡里奥·伊格莱西亚斯、{{link-en|羅貝托·卡洛斯 (歌手)|Roberto Carlos (singer)|羅貝托·卡洛斯}}、{{link-en|何塞·路易斯·罗德里格斯|José Luis Rodríguez}}等人统治着榜单。<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://books.google.com/?id=Rg8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA28&dq=jose+jose+el+principe+de+la+cancion#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=The Prince's 40-Year Reign: A Billboard Q&A |last=Cobo |first=Leila |volume=115 |issue=48 |page=28 |date=2003-11-29 |journal=[[Billboard_(magazine)|Billboard]] }}</ref>骚沙音乐受欢迎程度有所下降，它的音乐风格也发生了改变，拥有较慢的节奏且更注重浪漫的歌词。这被称为{{link-en|浪漫骚沙|salsa romantica}}时代。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Pietrobruno |first1=Sheenagh |title=Salsa and Its Transnational Moves |url=https://archive.org/details/salsaitstransnat0000piet |date=2006 |publisher=Lexington Books |location=Lanham |isbn=978-0-7391-6058-9}}</ref>

=== 20世纪90年代 ===
[[波丽露|波丽露]]音乐逐渐在年轻听众中流行起来。墨西哥歌手{{link-en|路易斯·米格尔|Luis Miguel}}以翻唱专辑《{{link-en|浪漫 (专辑)|Romance (Luis Miguel album)|浪漫}}》（1991）的成功赢得音乐事业的回春，<ref name="ageless">{{cite journal |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Ageless+romance+with+bolero.-a017482173 |title=Ageless Romance with Bolero |last=Holston |first=Mark |journal=Américas |date=1995-09-01 |accessdate=2015-03-21 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308053142/https://www.thefreelibrary.com/Ageless+romance+with+bolero.-a017482173 |dead-url=no }}</ref>截至90年代中期，拉丁流行音乐已经被年轻艺术家，如[[瑞奇·马丁|瑞奇·马丁]]、[[夏奇拉|夏奇拉]]以及胡里奥之子[[安立奎·伊格莱西亚斯|安立奎·伊格莱西亚斯]]所支配。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Powell |first1=John |title=Encyclopedia of North American immigration |date=2005 |publisher=Facts On File |location=New York |isbn=978-1-4381-1012-7 |page=92 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VNCX6UsdZYkC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA92#v=onepage&q&f=false |access-date=2019-08-14 |archive-date=2021-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210305150311/https://books.google.com/books?id=VNCX6UsdZYkC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA92#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>几乎同时，[[艾罗斯·拉玛佐第|艾罗斯·拉玛佐第]]、[[劳拉·普西妮|劳拉·普西妮]]以及{{link-en|Nek|Nek}}等[[意大利|意大利]]艺术家通过录制他们歌曲的西班牙语版本，成功地跨界到拉丁音乐界。<ref>{{cite news |last1=Obejas |first1=Achy |authorlink1=Achy Obejas |title=Italian Artists Conquer Latin Music Charts |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1999-04-04/news/9904040139_1_latin-music-eros-ramazzotti-italian |accessdate=2015-01-04 |work=[[Chicago_Tribune|Chicago Tribune]] |publisher=[[Tribune_Company|Tribune Company]] |date=1999-04-04 |archive-date=2015-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150104210953/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1999-04-04/news/9904040139_1_latin-music-eros-ramazzotti-italian |dead-url=no }}</ref>在墨西哥地区音乐领域，{{link-en|特哈诺音乐|Tejano}}成为最主要的流派。{{link-en|塞莱娜|Selena}}通过她的专辑《{{link-en|Entre a Mi Mundo|Entre a Mi Mundo}}》（1992，意为“进入我的世界”）和《{{link-en|Amor Prohibido|Amor Prohibido}}》（1994，意为“禁忌之爱”）助力特哈诺音乐进入主流市场，然而这一风潮在{{link-en|塞莱娜谋杀案|Murder of Selena|她去世}}后有所衰减。<ref>{{cite news |last1=Saldana |first1=Hector |title=Tejano music enjoyed a decade-long golden age |url=http://www.mysanantonio.com/news/local/article/Tejano-music-enjoyed-a-decade-long-golden-age-6447952.php |accessdate=2016-03-24 |work=[[San_Antonio_Express-News|San Antonio Express-News]] |date=2015-08-16 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308094252/https://www.mysanantonio.com/news/local/article/Tejano-music-enjoyed-a-decade-long-golden-age-6447952.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>在热带音乐领域，从80年代开始被注意到的{{link-en|梅伦格音乐|Merengue music}}走红，流行程度与骚沙媲美。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rodriguez |first1=Nelson |title=A look at contemporary Merengue. - Free Online Library |url=https://www.thefreelibrary.com/A+look+at+contemporary+Merengue-a021139246 |website=Latin Beat Magazine |publisher=thefreelibrary.com |accessdate=2019-07-07 |date=1998-09-01 |archive-date=2019-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190707130354/https://www.thefreelibrary.com/A%2Blook%2Bat%2Bcontemporary%2BMerengue-a021139246 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 21世纪00年代 ===
00年代中期，{{link-en|雷鬼冻|reggaeton}}开始流行于主流市场，{{link-en|泰戈·卡德龍|Tego Calderón}}、[[洋基老爹|洋基老爹]]、[[唐·奧馬爾|唐·奧馬爾]]以及{{link-en|威辛與揚戴爾|Wisin & Yandel}}被认为是这一类型的先驱。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Resto-Montero |first1=Gabriela |title=The Unstoppable Rise of Reggaeton |url=http://fusion.kinja.com/the-unstoppable-rise-of-reggaeton-1793854249 |website=Fusion |accessdate=2017-05-19 |date=2016-01-25 |archive-date=2017-06-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170602120452/http://fusion.kinja.com/the-unstoppable-rise-of-reggaeton-1793854249 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在热带音乐界，随着{{link-en|蒙奇与亚历山德拉|Monchy & Alexandra}}和{{link-en|Aventura (乐队)|Aventura (band)|Aventura}}等艺术家的{{link-en|巴恰达|bachata (music)}}音乐在拉丁美洲城市地区取得成功，这一曲风开始流行。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Cobo |first1=Leila |title=Tropical Paradise |journal=Billboard |date=2009-08-15 |volume=121 |issue=32 |page=31 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AHcbf1oaC8UC&lpg=PP1&pg=PT30#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2017-05-19 |issn=0006-2510 |archive-date=2020-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710001715/https://books.google.com/books?id=AHcbf1oaC8UC&lpg=PP1&pg=PT30#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{link-en|班达音乐|Banda (music)}}是这一时期墨西哥地区音乐的主要流派。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Henderson |first1=Alex |title=Me Cambiaste la Vida – Rogelio Martinez |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/me-cambiaste-la-vida-mw0000474613 |website=AllMusic |accessdate=2017-05-19 |archive-date=2021-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224222650/https://www.allmusic.com/album/me-cambiaste-la-vida-mw0000474613 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 21世纪10年代 ===
到了十年之际，拉丁音乐领域开始受快节奏支配，包括[[电子流行|电子流行]]、雷鬼冻、{{link-en|Urbano|Urbano music}}、班达和当代巴恰达音乐，而拉丁民谣及其歌手则在美国的拉丁电台节目中失宠。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cobo |first1=Leila |authorlink1=Leila Cobo |title=Latin Noise: We Want Our Ballads |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/6244251/latin-music-we-want-our-ballads |website=[[Billboard_(magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus_Global_Media|Prometheus Global Media]] |accessdate=2015-09-08 |date=2014-09-10 |archive-date=2021-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225094427/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/6244251/latin-music-we-want-our-ballads |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[流媒体|流媒体]]成为了美国、拉丁美洲与西班牙拉丁音乐产业的主要收入来源。<ref>{{cite news |last1=Melendez |first1=Angel |title=Why Are Spanish Songs More Popular on YouTube? Billboard's Leila Cobo Knows |url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/music/leila-cobo-talks-spanish-youtube-explosion-at-billboard-latin-music-conference-and-awards-2017-9293723 |accessdate=2017-06-12 |work=Miami New Times |date=2017-04-25 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308180209/https://www.miaminewtimes.com/music/leila-cobo-talks-spanish-youtube-explosion-at-billboard-latin-music-conference-and-awards-2017-9293723 |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{link-en|拉丁陷阱|Latin Trap}}在10年代中期受到了主流关注，知名艺术家有[[Ozuna|Ozuna]]、[[壞痞兔|壞痞兔]]和{{link-en|Anuel AA|Anuel AA}}等。<ref name="fader">{{cite web |title=Trap's Latin American Takeover |url=http://www.thefader.com/2017/07/05/traps-latin-american-takeover-spotify-playlist-trap-land |website=The Fader |accessdate=2017-12-29 |archive-date=2017-09-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915203944/http://www.thefader.com/2017/07/05/traps-latin-american-takeover-spotify-playlist-trap-land |dead-url=no }}</ref>

